 {"id":"bd-1jt.5","title":"Theme 5: Testing & Validation","description":"# Testing & Validation

## Purpose
Ensure all components of the fallback release system work correctly through comprehensive unit tests and E2E validation scripts.

## Testing Strategy

### 1. Unit Tests
Test individual functions in isolation:
- Platform detection
- Release freshness calculation
- Checksum verification
- Toolchain detection

### 2. Integration Tests
Test component interactions:
- Check → Build → Release pipeline
- Installer download → verify → install flow
- Remote SSH builds

### 3. E2E Tests
Full workflow tests in realistic environments:
- Docker containers for Linux
- macOS VM (if available) or actual Mac mini
- Windows via WSL

## Test Framework

Use bats (Bash Automated Testing System) for bash script tests:
\`\`\`bash
# Install
brew install bats-core  # macOS
apt install bats        # Ubuntu

# Run
bats tests/
\`\`\`

## Test Directory Structure
\`\`\`
tests/
├── unit/
│   ├── test_platform_detection.bats
│   ├── test_freshness_check.bats
│   ├── test_checksum_verify.bats
│   └── test_toolchain_detect.bats
├── integration/
│   ├── test_check_command.bats
│   ├── test_build_command.bats
│   └── test_release_command.bats
├── e2e/
│   ├── test_full_workflow.bats
│   ├── test_installer_linux.bats
│   └── test_installer_macos.bats
├── fixtures/
│   ├── mock_gh_responses/
│   └── sample_repos/
└── helpers/
    ├── mock_ssh.bash
    ├── mock_gh.bash
    └── common.bash
\`\`\`

## Logging Requirements

All tests must produce detailed logs:
\`\`\`bash
# In test helpers
setup() {
  TEST_LOG="\$BATS_TEST_TMPDIR/test.log"
  exec 3>&1 4>&2 1>"\$TEST_LOG" 2>&1
  echo "=== Test: \$BATS_TEST_NAME ==="
  echo "=== Started: \$(date -Iseconds) ==="
}

teardown() {
  echo "=== Ended: \$(date -Iseconds) ==="
  exec 1>&3 2>&4
  if [ "\$BATS_ERROR_STATUS" -ne 0 ]; then
    echo "Test failed! Log:"
    cat "\$TEST_LOG"
  fi
}
\`\`\`

## Key Test Scenarios

### Unit: Platform Detection
\`\`\`bash
@test "detect_platform on Linux x86_64" {
  # Mock uname
  function uname() { 
    case "\$1" in
      -s) echo "Linux" ;;
      -m) echo "x86_64" ;;
    esac
  }
  export -f uname

  run detect_platform
  assert_output --partial "linux-amd64"
}
\`\`\`

### Unit: Freshness Check
\`\`\`bash
@test "release 5 commits behind is fresh" {
  # Mock gh api to return ahead_by: 5
  function gh() { echo '{"ahead_by": 5}'; }
  export -f gh

  run check_freshness "v1.0.0"
  assert_success
}

@test "release 15 commits behind is stale" {
  function gh() { echo '{"ahead_by": 15}'; }
  export -f gh

  run check_freshness "v1.0.0"
  assert_failure
}
\`\`\`

### Integration: Build Command
\`\`\`bash
@test "dsr build ntm produces binary" {
  skip_if_no_toolchain "go"

  run dsr build ntm --target linux-amd64 --output-dir "\$BATS_TEST_TMPDIR"
  assert_success
  assert [ -f "\$BATS_TEST_TMPDIR/ntm-linux-amd64" ]
  assert [ -x "\$BATS_TEST_TMPDIR/ntm-linux-amd64" ]
}
\`\`\`

### E2E: Full Installer Flow
\`\`\`bash
@test "install.sh downloads and installs ntm" {
  # Run installer in Docker
  run docker run --rm ubuntu:22.04 bash -c "
    apt-get update && apt-get install -y curl
    curl -sSL file:///install.sh | bash -s -- --yes
    ntm --version
  "
  assert_success
  assert_output --partial "ntm"
}
\`\`\`

## CI Integration
Tests should run:
- On every commit to dsr repo
- Before each release
- Nightly for E2E tests (more expensive)

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] 100% unit test coverage for core functions
- [ ] Integration tests for all commands
- [ ] E2E tests for Linux installer
- [ ] All tests have detailed logging
- [ ] Tests run in <5 minutes (unit + integration)
